    • Method Detail

      • getPhoneStartTime

        long getPhoneStartTime()
        Returns the timestamp when the accumulation should start, in the phone reference. It corresponds to the beginning of the output file.
        Returns:
        the timestamp when the accumulation should start.

      • getPhoneStopTime

        long getPhoneStopTime()
        Returns the timestamp when the accumulation should stop, in the phone reference. It corresponds to the end of the output file.
        Returns:
        the timestamp when the accumulation should stop.

      • getDelay

        long getDelay()
        Returns the delay in milliseconds to add to a phone time to find the target time.
        Returns:
        the delay between the phone time and the target time.

      • getWindowWidthNano

        long getWindowWidthNano()
        Returns the width of the phone time window in nanoseconds. The time window is the set of samples that are used to calculate statistics in order to accumulate these samples into an epoch.
        Returns:
        the width of the phone time window in nanoseconds.

      • getEpochWidthNano

        long getEpochWidthNano()
        Returns the width of the phone epochs in nanoseconds. The epochs are the periods of time in the center of each time window that are associated with the accumulated values over this window. The epochs do not overlap, unlike the time windows.
        Returns:
        the width of the phone epochs in nanoseconds.

      • getWinBeginToEpBegin

        long getWinBeginToEpBegin()
        Returns the delay between the beginning of a time window and the beginning of the corresponding epoch.
        Returns:
        the delay between the beginning of a time window and the beginning of the corresponding epoch.
